-- Mazda announces new CEO, Ford executives to leave
-- 
-- Tue Nov 18, 2008 5:24am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/11/18/us-ford-mazda-personnel-sb-idUSTRE4AH2T520081118

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Mazda Motor Corp said on Tuesday that its Executive Vice President Takashi Yamanouchi is slated to become its new president and CEO, and it said two of the three board members sent from Ford Motor Co would leave. 

 Executive Vice President Philip Spender will remain on the board, while Chief Executive Hisakazu Imaki will become chairman when the personnel changes take place on November 19, Mazda said in a release. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )